- cook with lemon glaze (start that first)
- velvet chicken (for 500-600 g chicken breast fillets)
  - mix the following
    - 1 lightly whisked egg white
    - 1/2 tsp salt
    - 1 tbsp cornflour
    - 1 tbsp shaoxing
    - 1 tbsp peanut or veggie oil
- cut the chicken into strips, add to bowl and mix well
- refrigerate for 30 minutes
- bring 1 litre water and 1 tablespoon peanut or vegetable oil to a boil in a wok or a wide frying pan
- tip in the chicken and stir continuously for less than 1 minute until all the pieces look white
- tip the chicken and liquid through a colander and shake the colander
- refrigerate if you are not cooking straight away.

- prepare 500g warm (40°C) water with 2 tbsp cornflour
  - use this to birng things under control as required
- Make rice
- dry toast coarsely ground (+5) black pepper at 160°C
- add decent amount of oil
- add lots garlic and slow caramelise
- once moisture gone, temp up to 180 and add velvet chicken
- keep meat moving, add rice wine vinegar to deglaze
- add lemon syrup
- add some starch water to desired consistency
- add sliced & slivered (white and green) spring onions
